Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also uses convex programming, which is a popular optimization technique in machine learning and statistics, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper involves numerical computations and analysis, which could fall under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
